# This is a meta-repo — no code lives here. The .gitignore exists only to
# protect against accidental commits of OS metadata, IDE state, or — most
# importantly — secrets if anyone clones it locally and reuses the directory.

# OS metadata
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# IDE / editor
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo

# Secrets — defense in depth. Real secret hygiene is "don't put them in the
# repo directory at all," but if one slips in, git refuses to track these.
.env
.env.*
*.key
*.pem
.sr_key
.npmrc
secrets/

# Stale leftovers from the pre-split monorepo working tree. If anyone clones
# this repo on top of an old workspace, these directories hold node_modules
# and build artifacts from packages that have moved out — keep them ignored
# so a careless `git add -A` doesn't try to re-add deleted code.
node_modules/
dist/
integrations/
packages/

# Runtime artifacts that have no place in a code-free meta-repo.
*.log
fly-*.log
